Prices for Used Cars, Plane Tickets 
and Electricity Eased in November

slides.speech: The consumer-price index rose 7.1% in November from a year earlier, the smallest increase since December, the Labor Department said Tuesday. On a monthly basis, the November CPI increased a seasonally adjusted 0.1% from October.

from October.

slides.speech:
The CPI measures the prices consumers pay for goods and services.

While many prices remain higher than they were a year ago, prices have started to ease on a monthly basis in a potential sign that price pressures are easing.
